31bool isAtomicLoadOp(AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op) {
32 return Op == AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load ||
33 Op == AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load ||
34 Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load ||
35 Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n;
36}
37
38bool isAtomicStoreOp(AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op) {
39 return Op == AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store ||
40 Op == AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store ||
41 Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store ||
42 Op == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n;
43}

45 class AtomicInfo {
46 CodeGenFunction &CGF;
47 QualType AtomicTy;
48 QualType ValueTy;
49 uint64_t AtomicSizeInBits;
50 uint64_t ValueSizeInBits;
51 CharUnits AtomicAlign;
52 CharUnits ValueAlign;
53 TypeEvaluationKind EvaluationKind;
54 bool UseLibcall;
55 LValue LVal;
56 CGBitFieldInfo BFI;
57 public:
58 AtomicInfo(CodeGenFunction &CGF, LValue &lvalue, AtomicExpr::AtomicOp Op)
59 : CGF(CGF), AtomicSizeInBits(0), ValueSizeInBits(0),
60 EvaluationKind(TEK_Scalar), UseLibcall(true) {
61 assert(!lvalue.isGlobalReg());
62 ASTContext &C = CGF.getContext();
63 if (lvalue.isSimple()) {
64 AtomicTy = lvalue.getType();
65 if (auto *ATy = AtomicTy->getAs<AtomicType>())
66 ValueTy = ATy->getValueType();
67 else
68 ValueTy = AtomicTy;
69 EvaluationKind = CGF.getEvaluationKind(ValueTy);
70
71 uint64_t ValueAlignInBits;
72 uint64_t AtomicAlignInBits;
73 TypeInfo ValueTI = C.getTypeInfo(ValueTy);
74 ValueSizeInBits = ValueTI.Width;
75 ValueAlignInBits = ValueTI.Align;
76
77 TypeInfo AtomicTI = C.getTypeInfo(AtomicTy);
78 AtomicSizeInBits = AtomicTI.Width;
79 AtomicAlignInBits = AtomicTI.Align;
80
81 assert(ValueSizeInBits <= AtomicSizeInBits);
82 assert(ValueAlignInBits <= AtomicAlignInBits);
83
84 AtomicAlign = C.toCharUnitsFromBits(AtomicAlignInBits);
85 ValueAlign = C.toCharUnitsFromBits(ValueAlignInBits);
86 if (lvalue.getAlignment().isZero())
87 lvalue.setAlignment(AtomicAlign);
88
89 LVal = lvalue;
90 } else if (lvalue.isBitField()) {
91 ValueTy = lvalue.getType();
92 ValueSizeInBits = C.getTypeSize(ValueTy);
93 auto &OrigBFI = lvalue.getBitFieldInfo();
94 auto Offset = OrigBFI.Offset % C.toBits(lvalue.getAlignment());
95 AtomicSizeInBits = C.toBits(
96 C.toCharUnitsFromBits(Offset + OrigBFI.Size + C.getCharWidth() - 1)
97 .alignTo(lvalue.getAlignment()));
98 auto VoidPtrAddr = CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(lvalue.getBitFieldPointer());
99 auto OffsetInChars =
100 (C.toCharUnitsFromBits(OrigBFI.Offset) / lvalue.getAlignment()) *
101 lvalue.getAlignment();
102 VoidPtrAddr = CGF.Builder.CreateConstGEP1_64(
103 VoidPtrAddr, OffsetInChars.getQuantity());
104 auto Addr = CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
105 VoidPtrAddr,
106 CGF.Builder.getIntNTy(AtomicSizeInBits)->getPointerTo(
107 CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS()),
108 "atomic_bitfield_base");
109 BFI = OrigBFI;
110 BFI.Offset = Offset;
111 BFI.StorageSize = AtomicSizeInBits;
112 BFI.StorageOffset += OffsetInChars;
113 LVal = LValue::MakeBitfield(Address(Addr, lvalue.getAlignment()),
114 BFI, lvalue.getType(), lvalue.getBaseInfo(),
115 lvalue.getTBAAInfo());
116 AtomicTy = C.getIntTypeForBitwidth(AtomicSizeInBits, OrigBFI.IsSigned);
117 if (AtomicTy.isNull()) {
118 llvm::APInt Size(
119 /*numBits=*/32,
120 C.toCharUnitsFromBits(AtomicSizeInBits).getQuantity());
121 AtomicTy = C.getConstantArrayType(C.CharTy, Size, ArrayType::Normal,
122 /*IndexTypeQuals=*/0);
123 }
124 AtomicAlign = ValueAlign = lvalue.getAlignment();
125 } else if (lvalue.isVectorElt()) {
126 ValueTy = lvalue.getType()->getAs<VectorType>()->getElementType();
127 ValueSizeInBits = C.getTypeSize(ValueTy);
128 AtomicTy = lvalue.getType();
129 AtomicSizeInBits = C.getTypeSize(AtomicTy);
130 AtomicAlign = ValueAlign = lvalue.getAlignment();
131 LVal = lvalue;
132 } else {
133 assert(lvalue.isExtVectorElt());
134 ValueTy = lvalue.getType();
135 ValueSizeInBits = C.getTypeSize(ValueTy);
136 AtomicTy = ValueTy = CGF.getContext().getExtVectorType(
137 lvalue.getType(), lvalue.getExtVectorAddress()
138 .getElementType()->getVectorNumElements());
139 AtomicSizeInBits = C.getTypeSize(AtomicTy);
140 AtomicAlign = ValueAlign = lvalue.getAlignment();
141 LVal = lvalue;
142 }
143 UseLibcall = !C.getTargetInfo().hasBuiltinAtomic(
144 AtomicSizeInBits, C.toBits(lvalue.getAlignment()));
145 if (AtomicTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.CGM.getContext())) {
146 if (CGF.getTarget().areAllPointersCapabilities())
147 UseLibcall =
148 CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().cheriCapabilityAtomicNeedsLibcall(
149 Op);
150 else
151 // XXXAR: currently always use libcalls in hybrid since we generate
152 // invalid code and assert otherwise.
153 UseLibcall = true;
154 }
155 }
156
157 QualType getAtomicType() const { return AtomicTy; }
158 QualType getValueType() const { return ValueTy; }
159 CharUnits getAtomicAlignment() const { return AtomicAlign; }
160 uint64_t getAtomicSizeInBits() const { return AtomicSizeInBits; }
161 uint64_t getValueSizeInBits() const { return ValueSizeInBits; }
162 TypeEvaluationKind getEvaluationKind() const { return EvaluationKind; }
163 bool shouldUseLibcall() const { return UseLibcall; }
164 const LValue &getAtomicLValue() const { return LVal; }
165 llvm::Value *getAtomicPointer() const {
166 if (LVal.isSimple())
167 return LVal.getPointer();
168 else if (LVal.isBitField())
169 return LVal.getBitFieldPointer();
170 else if (LVal.isVectorElt())
171 return LVal.getVectorPointer();
172 assert(LVal.isExtVectorElt());
173 return LVal.getExtVectorPointer();
174 }
175 Address getAtomicAddress() const {
176 return Address(getAtomicPointer(), getAtomicAlignment());
177 }
178
179 Address getAtomicAddressAsAtomicIntPointer() const {
180 return emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(getAtomicAddress());
181 }

183 /// Is the atomic size larger than the underlying value type?
184 ///
185 /// Note that the absence of padding does not mean that atomic
186 /// objects are completely interchangeable with non-atomic
187 /// objects: we might have promoted the alignment of a type
188 /// without making it bigger.
189 bool hasPadding() const {
190 return (ValueSizeInBits != AtomicSizeInBits);
191 }
192
193 bool emitMemSetZeroIfNecessary() const;
194
195 llvm::Value *getAtomicSizeValue() const {
196 CharUnits size = CGF.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(AtomicSizeInBits);
197 return CGF.CGM.getSize(size);
198 }

223 /// Project an l-value down to the value field.
224 LValue projectValue() const {
225 assert(LVal.isSimple());
226 Address addr = getAtomicAddress();
227 if (hasPadding())
228 addr = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, 0);
229
230 return LValue::MakeAddr(addr, getValueType(), CGF.getContext(),
231 LVal.getBaseInfo(), LVal.getTBAAInfo());
232 }

314Address AtomicInfo::CreateTempAlloca() const {
315 Address TempAlloca = CGF.CreateMemTemp(
316 (LVal.isBitField() && ValueSizeInBits > AtomicSizeInBits) ? ValueTy
317 : AtomicTy,
318 getAtomicAlignment(),
319 "atomic-temp");
320 // Cast to pointer to value type for bitfields.
321 if (LVal.isBitField())
322 return CGF.Builder.CreatePointerBitCastOrAddrSpaceCast(
323 TempAlloca, getAtomicAddress().getType());
324 return TempAlloca;
325}

327static RValue emitAtomicLibcall(CodeGenFunction &CGF,
328 StringRef fnName,
329 QualType resultType,
330 CallArgList &args) {
331 const CGFunctionInfo &fnInfo =
332 CGF.CGM.getTypes().arrangeBuiltinFunctionCall(resultType, args);
333 llvm::FunctionType *fnTy = CGF.CGM.getTypes().GetFunctionType(fnInfo);
334 llvm::FunctionCallee fn = CGF.CGM.CreateRuntimeFunction(fnTy, fnName);
335 auto callee = CGCallee::forDirect(fn);
336 return CGF.EmitCall(fnInfo, callee, ReturnValueSlot(), args);
337}

339/// Does a store of the given IR type modify the full expected width?
340static bool isFullSizeType(CodeGenModule &CGM, llvm::Type *type,
341 uint64_t expectedSize) {
342 return (CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(type) * 8 == expectedSize);
343}
344
345/// Does the atomic type require memsetting to zero before initialization?
346///
347/// The IR type is provided as a way of making certain queries faster.
348bool AtomicInfo::requiresMemSetZero(llvm::Type *type) const {
349 // If the atomic type has size padding, we definitely need a memset.
350 if (hasPadding()) return true;
351
352 // Otherwise, do some simple heuristics to try to avoid it:
353 switch (getEvaluationKind()) {
354 // For scalars and complexes, check whether the store size of the
355 // type uses the full size.
356 case TEK_Scalar:
357 return !isFullSizeType(CGF.CGM, type, AtomicSizeInBits);
358 case TEK_Complex:
359 return !isFullSizeType(CGF.CGM, type->getStructElementType(0),
360 AtomicSizeInBits / 2);
361
362 // Padding in structs has an undefined bit pattern. User beware.
363 case TEK_Aggregate:
364 return false;
365 }
366 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
367}
368
369bool AtomicInfo::emitMemSetZeroIfNecessary() const {
370 assert(LVal.isSimple());
371 llvm::Value *addr = LVal.getPointer();
372 if (!requiresMemSetZero(addr->getType()->getPointerElementType()))
373 return false;
374
375 CGF.Builder.CreateMemSet(
376 addr, llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.Int8Ty, 0),
377 CGF.getContext().toCharUnitsFromBits(AtomicSizeInBits).getQuantity(),
378 LVal.getAlignment().getQuantity());
379 return true;
380}

382static void emitAtomicCmpXchg(CodeGenFunction &CGF, AtomicExpr *E, bool IsWeak,
383 Address Dest, Address Ptr,
384 Address Val1, Address Val2,
385 uint64_t Size,
386 llvm::AtomicOrdering SuccessOrder,
387 llvm::AtomicOrdering FailureOrder,
388 llvm::SyncScope::ID Scope) {
389 // Note that cmpxchg doesn't support weak cmpxchg, at least at the moment.
390 llvm::Value *Expected = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Val1);
391 llvm::Value *Desired = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Val2);
392
393 llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst *Pair = CGF.Builder.CreateAtomicCmpXchg(
394 Ptr.getPointer(), Expected, Desired, SuccessOrder, FailureOrder,
395 Scope);
396 Pair->setVolatile(E->isVolatile());
397 Pair->setWeak(IsWeak);
398
399 // Cmp holds the result of the compare-exchange operation: true on success,
400 // false on failure.
401 llvm::Value *Old = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractValue(Pair, 0);
402 llvm::Value *Cmp = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractValue(Pair, 1);
403
404 // This basic block is used to hold the store instruction if the operation
405 // failed.
406 llvm::BasicBlock *StoreExpectedBB =
407 CGF.createBasicBlock("cmpxchg.store_expected", CGF.CurFn);
408
409 // This basic block is the exit point of the operation, we should end up
410 // here regardless of whether or not the operation succeeded.
411 llvm::BasicBlock *ContinueBB =
412 CGF.createBasicBlock("cmpxchg.continue", CGF.CurFn);
413
414 // Update Expected if Expected isn't equal to Old, otherwise branch to the
415 // exit point.
416 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Cmp, ContinueBB, StoreExpectedBB);
417
418 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(StoreExpectedBB);
419 // Update the memory at Expected with Old's value.
420 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Old, Val1);
421 // Finally, branch to the exit point.
422 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContinueBB);
423
424 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContinueBB);
425 // Update the memory at Dest with Cmp's value.
426 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(Cmp, CGF.MakeAddrLValue(Dest, E->getType()));
427}
428
429/// Given an ordering required on success, emit all possible cmpxchg
430/// instructions to cope with the provided (but possibly only dynamically known)
431/// FailureOrder.
432static void emitAtomicCmpXchgFailureSet(CodeGenFunction &CGF, AtomicExpr *E,
433 bool IsWeak, Address Dest, Address Ptr,
434 Address Val1, Address Val2,
435 llvm::Value *FailureOrderVal,
436 uint64_t Size,
437 llvm::AtomicOrdering SuccessOrder,
438 llvm::SyncScope::ID Scope) {
439 llvm::AtomicOrdering FailureOrder;
440 if (llvm::ConstantInt *FO = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(FailureOrderVal)) {
441 auto FOS = FO->getSExtValue();
442 if (!llvm::isValidAtomicOrderingCABI(FOS))
443 FailureOrder = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic;
444 else
445 switch ((llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI)FOS) {
446 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::relaxed:
447 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::release:
448 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel:
449 FailureOrder = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic;
450 break;
451 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume:
452 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire:
453 FailureOrder = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire;
454 break;
455 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::seq_cst:
456 FailureOrder = llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
457 break;
458 }
459 if (isStrongerThan(FailureOrder, SuccessOrder)) {
460 // Don't assert on undefined behavior "failure argument shall be no
461 // stronger than the success argument".
462 FailureOrder =
463 llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(SuccessOrder);
464 }
465 emitAtomicCmpXchg(CGF, E, IsWeak, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, Size, SuccessOrder,
466 FailureOrder, Scope);
467 return;
468 }
469
470 // Create all the relevant BB's
471 llvm::BasicBlock *MonotonicBB = nullptr, *AcquireBB = nullptr,
472 *SeqCstBB = nullptr;
473 MonotonicBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("monotonic_fail", CGF.CurFn);
474 if (SuccessOrder != llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic &&
475 SuccessOrder != llvm::AtomicOrdering::Release)
476 AcquireBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("acquire_fail", CGF.CurFn);
477 if (SuccessOrder == llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent)
478 SeqCstBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("seqcst_fail", CGF.CurFn);
479
480 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic.continue", CGF.CurFn);
481
482 llvm::SwitchInst *SI = CGF.Builder.CreateSwitch(FailureOrderVal, MonotonicBB);
483
484 // Emit all the different atomics
485
486 // MonotonicBB is arbitrarily chosen as the default case; in practice, this
487 // doesn't matter unless someone is crazy enough to use something that
488 // doesn't fold to a constant for the ordering.
489 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(MonotonicBB);
490 emitAtomicCmpXchg(CGF, E, IsWeak, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2,
491 Size, SuccessOrder, llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, Scope);
492 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
493
494 if (AcquireBB) {
495 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(AcquireBB);
496 emitAtomicCmpXchg(CGF, E, IsWeak, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2,
497 Size, SuccessOrder, llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire, Scope);
498 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
499 SI->addCase(CGF.Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume),
500 AcquireBB);
501 SI->addCase(CGF.Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire),
502 AcquireBB);
503 }
504 if (SeqCstBB) {
505 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(SeqCstBB);
506 emitAtomicCmpXchg(CGF, E, IsWeak, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, Size, SuccessOrder,
507 llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent, Scope);
508 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
509 SI->addCase(CGF.Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::seq_cst),
510 SeqCstBB);
511 }
512
513 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContBB);
514}

516static void EmitAtomicOp(CodeGenFunction &CGF, AtomicExpr *E, Address Dest,
517 Address Ptr, Address Val1, Address Val2,
518 llvm::Value *IsWeak, llvm::Value *FailureOrder,
519 uint64_t Size, llvm::AtomicOrdering Order,
520 llvm::SyncScope::ID Scope) {
521 llvm::AtomicRMWInst::BinOp Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add;
522 llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps PostOp = (llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps)0;
523
524 switch (E->getOp()) {
525 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
526 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init:
527 llvm_unreachable("Already handled!");
528
529 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
530 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
531 emitAtomicCmpXchgFailureSet(CGF, E, false, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2,
532 FailureOrder, Size, Order, Scope);
533 return;
534 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
535 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
536 emitAtomicCmpXchgFailureSet(CGF, E, true, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2,
537 FailureOrder, Size, Order, Scope);
538 return;
539 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange:
540 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n: {
541 if (llvm::ConstantInt *IsWeakC = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(IsWeak)) {
542 emitAtomicCmpXchgFailureSet(CGF, E, IsWeakC->getZExtValue(), Dest, Ptr,
543 Val1, Val2, FailureOrder, Size, Order, Scope);
544 } else {
545 // Create all the relevant BB's
546 llvm::BasicBlock *StrongBB =
547 CGF.createBasicBlock("cmpxchg.strong", CGF.CurFn);
548 llvm::BasicBlock *WeakBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("cmxchg.weak", CGF.CurFn);
549 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB =
550 CGF.createBasicBlock("cmpxchg.continue", CGF.CurFn);
551
552 llvm::SwitchInst *SI = CGF.Builder.CreateSwitch(IsWeak, WeakBB);
553 SI->addCase(CGF.Builder.getInt1(false), StrongBB);
554
555 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(StrongBB);
556 emitAtomicCmpXchgFailureSet(CGF, E, false, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2,
557 FailureOrder, Size, Order, Scope);
558 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
559
560 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(WeakBB);
561 emitAtomicCmpXchgFailureSet(CGF, E, true, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2,
562 FailureOrder, Size, Order, Scope);
563 CGF.Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
564
565 CGF.Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContBB);
566 }
567 return;
568 }
569 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
570 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load:
571 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
572 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load: {
573 llvm::LoadInst *Load = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Ptr);
574 Load->setAtomic(Order, Scope);
575 Load->setVolatile(E->isVolatile());
576 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Load, Dest);
577 return;
578 }
579
580 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
581 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store:
582 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
583 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n: {
584 llvm::Value *LoadVal1 = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Val1);
585 llvm::StoreInst *Store = CGF.Builder.CreateStore(LoadVal1, Ptr);
586 Store->setAtomic(Order, Scope);
587 Store->setVolatile(E->isVolatile());
588 return;
589 }
590
591 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_exchange:
592 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_exchange:
593 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n:
594 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange:
595 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xchg;
596 break;
597
598 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_add_fetch:
599 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Add;
600 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
601 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_add:
602 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_add:
603 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_add:
604 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Add;
605 break;
606
607 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_sub_fetch:
608 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Sub;
609 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
610 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_sub:
611 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_sub:
612 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_sub:
613 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Sub;
614 break;
615
616 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_min:
617 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_min:
618 Op = E->getValueType()->isSignedIntegerType() ? llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Min
619 : llvm::AtomicRMWInst::UMin;
620 break;
621
622 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_max:
623 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_max:
624 Op = E->getValueType()->isSignedIntegerType() ? llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Max
625 : llvm::AtomicRMWInst::UMax;
626 break;
627
628 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_and_fetch:
629 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::And;
630 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
631 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_and:
632 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_and:
633 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_and:
634 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::And;
635 break;
636
637 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_or_fetch:
638 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Or;
639 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
640 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_or:
641 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_or:
642 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_or:
643 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Or;
644 break;
645
646 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_xor_fetch:
647 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Xor;
648 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
649 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_xor:
650 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_xor:
651 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_xor:
652 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Xor;
653 break;
654
655 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch:
656 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::And; // the NOT is special cased below
657 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
658 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_nand:
659 Op = llvm::AtomicRMWInst::Nand;
660 break;
661 }
662
663 llvm::Value *LoadVal1 = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Val1);
664 llvm::AtomicRMWInst *RMWI =
665 CGF.Builder.CreateAtomicRMW(Op, Ptr.getPointer(), LoadVal1, Order, Scope);
666 RMWI->setVolatile(E->isVolatile());
667
668 // For __atomic_*_fetch operations, perform the operation again to
669 // determine the value which was written.
670 llvm::Value *Result = RMWI;
671 if (PostOp)
672 Result = CGF.Builder.CreateBinOp(PostOp, RMWI, LoadVal1);
673 if (E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch)
674 Result = CGF.Builder.CreateNot(Result);
675 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(Result, Dest);
676}
677
678// This function emits any expression (scalar, complex, or aggregate)
679// into a temporary alloca.
680static Address
681EmitValToTemp(CodeGenFunction &CGF, Expr *E) {
682 Address DeclPtr = CGF.CreateMemTemp(E->getType(), ".atomictmp");
683 CGF.EmitAnyExprToMem(E, DeclPtr, E->getType().getQualifiers(),
684 /*Init*/ true);
685 return DeclPtr;
686}
687
688static void EmitAtomicOp(CodeGenFunction &CGF, AtomicExpr *Expr, Address Dest,
689 Address Ptr, Address Val1, Address Val2,
690 llvm::Value *IsWeak, llvm::Value *FailureOrder,
691 uint64_t Size, llvm::AtomicOrdering Order,
692 llvm::Value *Scope) {
693 auto ScopeModel = Expr->getScopeModel();
694
695 // LLVM atomic instructions always have synch scope. If clang atomic
696 // expression has no scope operand, use default LLVM synch scope.
697 if (!ScopeModel) {
698 EmitAtomicOp(CGF, Expr, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, FailureOrder, Size,
699 Order, CGF.CGM.getLLVMContext().getOrInsertSyncScopeID(""));
700 return;
701 }
702
703 // Handle constant scope.
704 if (auto SC = dyn_cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Scope)) {
705 auto SCID = CGF.getTargetHooks().getLLVMSyncScopeID(
706 CGF.CGM.getLangOpts(), ScopeModel->map(SC->getZExtValue()),
707 Order, CGF.CGM.getLLVMContext());
708 EmitAtomicOp(CGF, Expr, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, FailureOrder, Size,
709 Order, SCID);
710 return;
711 }
712
713 // Handle non-constant scope.
714 auto &Builder = CGF.Builder;
715 auto Scopes = ScopeModel->getRuntimeValues();
716 llvm::DenseMap<unsigned, llvm::BasicBlock *> BB;
717 for (auto S : Scopes)
718 BB[S] = CGF.createBasicBlock(getAsString(ScopeModel->map(S)), CGF.CurFn);
719
720 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB =
721 CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic.scope.continue", CGF.CurFn);
722
723 auto *SC = Builder.CreateIntCast(Scope, Builder.getInt32Ty(), false);
724 // If unsupported synch scope is encountered at run time, assume a fallback
725 // synch scope value.
726 auto FallBack = ScopeModel->getFallBackValue();
727 llvm::SwitchInst *SI = Builder.CreateSwitch(SC, BB[FallBack]);
728 for (auto S : Scopes) {
729 auto *B = BB[S];
730 if (S != FallBack)
731 SI->addCase(Builder.getInt32(S), B);
732
733 Builder.SetInsertPoint(B);
734 EmitAtomicOp(CGF, Expr, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, FailureOrder, Size,
735 Order,
736 CGF.getTargetHooks().getLLVMSyncScopeID(CGF.CGM.getLangOpts(),
737 ScopeModel->map(S),
738 Order,
739 CGF.getLLVMContext()));
740 Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
741 }
742
743 Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContBB);
744}
745
746static void
747AddDirectArgument(CodeGenFunction &CGF, CallArgList &Args,
748 bool UseOptimizedLibcall, llvm::Value *Val, QualType ValTy,
749 SourceLocation Loc, CharUnits SizeInChars) {
750 if (UseOptimizedLibcall) {
751 // Load value and pass it to the function directly.
752 if (ValTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
753 // capabilities can be passed directly without casting to i8*
754 Args.add(RValue::get(Val), ValTy);
755 return;
756 }
757 CharUnits Align = CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(ValTy);
758 int64_t SizeInBits = CGF.getContext().toBits(SizeInChars);
759 ValTy =
760 CGF.getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(SizeInBits, /*Signed=*/false);
761 llvm::Type *IPtrTy =
762 llvm::IntegerType::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), SizeInBits)->getPointerTo(
763 CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS());
764 Address Ptr = Address(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, IPtrTy), Align);
765 Val = CGF.EmitLoadOfScalar(Ptr, false,
766 CGF.getContext().getPointerType(ValTy),
767 Loc);
768 // Coerce the value into an appropriately sized integer type.
769 Args.add(RValue::get(Val), ValTy);
770 } else {
771 if (false && ValTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
772 // capabilities can be passed directly without casting to i8*
773 Args.add(RValue::get(Val), ValTy);
774 } else {
775 // Non-optimized functions always take a reference.
776 Args.add(RValue::get(CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(Val)),
777 CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
778 }
779 }
780}
781
782RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicExpr(AtomicExpr *E) {
783 QualType AtomicTy = E->getPtr()->getType()->getPointeeType();
784 QualType MemTy = AtomicTy;
785 if (const AtomicType *AT = AtomicTy->getAs<AtomicType>())
786 MemTy = AT->getValueType();
787 llvm::Value *IsWeak = nullptr, *OrderFail = nullptr;
788
789 Address Val1 = Address::invalid();
790 Address Val2 = Address::invalid();
791 Address Dest = Address::invalid();
792 Address Ptr = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getPtr());
793
794 if (E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init ||
795 E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init) {
796 LValue lvalue = MakeAddrLValue(Ptr, AtomicTy);
797 EmitAtomicInit(E->getVal1(), lvalue);
798 return RValue::get(nullptr);
799 }
800
801 CharUnits sizeChars, alignChars;
802 std::tie(sizeChars, alignChars) = getContext().getTypeInfoInChars(AtomicTy);
803 uint64_t Size = sizeChars.getQuantity();
804 unsigned MaxInlineWidthInBits = getTarget().getMaxAtomicInlineWidth();
805
806 bool Oversized = getContext().toBits(sizeChars) > MaxInlineWidthInBits;
807 bool Misaligned = (Ptr.getAlignment() % sizeChars) != 0;
808 bool UseLibcall = Misaligned | Oversized;
809
810 bool IsCheriCap = AtomicTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGM.getContext());
811 if (IsCheriCap) {
812 if (getTarget().areAllPointersCapabilities())
813 UseLibcall = CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().cheriCapabilityAtomicNeedsLibcall(
814 E->getOp());
815 else
816 // XXXAR: currently always use libcalls in hybrid since we generate
817 // invalid code and assert otherwise.
818 UseLibcall = true;
819 }
820
821 if (UseLibcall) {
822 CGM.getDiags().Report(E->getBeginLoc(), diag::warn_atomic_op_misaligned)
823 << !Oversized;
824 }
825
826 llvm::Value *Order = EmitScalarExpr(E->getOrder());
827 llvm::Value *Scope =
828 E->getScopeModel() ? EmitScalarExpr(E->getScope()) : nullptr;
829
830 switch (E->getOp()) {
831 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
832 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init:
833 llvm_unreachable("Already handled above with EmitAtomicInit!");
834
835 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
836 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load:
837 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
838 break;
839
840 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load:
841 Dest = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getVal1());
842 break;
843
844 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
845 Val1 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getVal1());
846 break;
847
848 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange:
849 Val1 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getVal1());
850 Dest = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getVal2());
851 break;
852
853 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
854 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
855 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
856 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
857 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n:
858 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange:
859 Val1 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getVal1());
860 if (E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange)
861 Val2 = EmitPointerWithAlignment(E->getVal2());
862 else
863 Val2 = EmitValToTemp(*this, E->getVal2());
864 OrderFail = EmitScalarExpr(E->getOrderFail());
865 if (E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n ||
866 E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange)
867 IsWeak = EmitScalarExpr(E->getWeak());
868 break;
869
870 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_add:
871 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_sub:
872 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_add:
873 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_sub:
874 if (MemTy->isPointerType()) {
875 // For pointer arithmetic, we're required to do a bit of math:
876 // adding 1 to an int* is not the same as adding 1 to a uintptr_t.
877 // ... but only for the C11 builtins. The GNU builtins expect the
878 // user to multiply by sizeof(T).
879 QualType Val1Ty = E->getVal1()->getType();
880 llvm::Value *Val1Scalar = EmitScalarExpr(E->getVal1());
881 CharUnits PointeeIncAmt =
882 getContext().getTypeSizeInChars(MemTy->getPointeeType());
883 Val1Scalar = Builder.CreateMul(Val1Scalar, CGM.getSize(PointeeIncAmt));
884 auto Temp = CreateMemTemp(Val1Ty, ".atomictmp");
885 Val1 = Temp;
886 EmitStoreOfScalar(Val1Scalar, MakeAddrLValue(Temp, Val1Ty));
887 break;
888 }
889 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
890 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_add:
891 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_sub:
892 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_add_fetch:
893 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_sub_fetch:
894 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
895 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_exchange:
896 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store:
897 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_exchange:
898 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n:
899 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n:
900 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_and:
901 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_or:
902 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_xor:
903 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_and:
904 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_or:
905 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_xor:
906 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_min:
907 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_max:
908 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_and:
909 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_or:
910 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_xor:
911 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_nand:
912 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_and_fetch:
913 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_or_fetch:
914 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_xor_fetch:
915 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch:
916 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_min:
917 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_max:
918 Val1 = EmitValToTemp(*this, E->getVal1());
919 break;
920 }
921
922 QualType RValTy = E->getType().getUnqualifiedType();
923
924 // The inlined atomics only function on iN types, where N is a power of 2. We
925 // need to make sure (via temporaries if necessary) that all incoming values
926 // are compatible.
927 LValue AtomicVal = MakeAddrLValue(Ptr, AtomicTy);
928 AtomicInfo Atomics(*this, AtomicVal, E->getOp());
929 assert(Atomics.shouldUseLibcall() == UseLibcall);
930
931 Ptr = Atomics.emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Ptr);
932 if (Val1.isValid()) Val1 = Atomics.convertToAtomicIntPointer(Val1);
933 if (Val2.isValid()) Val2 = Atomics.convertToAtomicIntPointer(Val2);
934 if (Dest.isValid())
935 Dest = Atomics.emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Dest);
936 else if (E->isCmpXChg())
937 Dest = CreateMemTemp(RValTy, "cmpxchg.bool");
938 else if (!RValTy->isVoidType())
939 Dest = Atomics.emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Atomics.CreateTempAlloca());
940
941 bool IsStore = isAtomicStoreOp(E->getOp());
942 bool IsLoad = isAtomicLoadOp(E->getOp());
943
944 // Use a library call. See: http://gcc.gnu.org/wiki/Atomic/GCCMM/LIbrary .
945 if (UseLibcall) {
946 bool UseOptimizedLibcall = false;
947 switch (E->getOp()) {
948 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
949 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init:
950 llvm_unreachable("Already handled above with EmitAtomicInit!");
951
952 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_add:
953 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_add:
954 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_add:
955 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_and:
956 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_and:
957 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_and:
958 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_or:
959 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_or:
960 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_or:
961 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_nand:
962 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_sub:
963 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_sub:
964 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_sub:
965 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_xor:
966 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_xor:
967 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_min:
968 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_max:
969 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_xor:
970 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_add_fetch:
971 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_and_fetch:
972 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch:
973 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_or_fetch:
974 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_sub_fetch:
975 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_xor_fetch:
976 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_min:
977 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_max:
978 // For these, only library calls for certain sizes exist.
979 UseOptimizedLibcall = true;
980 break;
981
982 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load:
983 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
984 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange:
985 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange:
986 // Use the generic version if we don't know that the operand will be
987 // suitably aligned for the optimized version.
988 if (Misaligned)
989 break;
990 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
991 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
992 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
993 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_exchange:
994 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
995 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
996 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load:
997 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store:
998 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_exchange:
999 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
1000 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
1001 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
1002 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n:
1003 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n:
1004 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n:
1005 // Only use optimized library calls for sizes for which they exist.
1006 // FIXME: Size == 16 optimized library functions exist too.
1007 if (!IsCheriCap && (Size == 1 || Size == 2 || Size == 4 || Size == 8))
1008 UseOptimizedLibcall = true;
1009 break;
1010 }
1011
1012 CallArgList Args;
1013 if (!UseOptimizedLibcall) {
1014 // For non-optimized library calls, the size is the first parameter
1015 Args.add(RValue::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(SizeTy, Size)),
1016 getContext().getSizeType());
1017 }
1018 // Atomic address is the first or second parameter
1019 // The OpenCL atomic library functions only accept pointer arguments to
1020 // generic address space.
1021 auto CastToGenericAddrSpace = [&](llvm::Value *V, QualType PT) {
1022 if (!E->isOpenCL())
1023 return V;
1024 auto AS = PT->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType().getAddressSpace();
1025 if (AS == LangAS::opencl_generic)
1026 return V;
1027 auto DestAS = CGM.getTargetAddressSpace(LangAS::opencl_generic);
1028 auto T = V->getType();
1029 auto *DestType = T->getPointerElementType()->getPointerTo(DestAS);
1030
1031 return getTargetHooks().performAddrSpaceCast(
1032 *this, V, AS, LangAS::opencl_generic, DestType, false);
1033 };
1034
1035 Args.add(RValue::get(CastToGenericAddrSpace(
1036 EmitCastToVoidPtr(Ptr.getPointer()), E->getPtr()->getType())),
1037 getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1038
1039 std::string LibCallName;
1040 QualType LoweredMemTy =
1041 MemTy->isPointerType() ? getContext().getIntPtrType() : MemTy;
1042 QualType RetTy;
1043 bool HaveRetTy = false;
1044 llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps PostOp = (llvm::Instruction::BinaryOps)0;
1045 switch (E->getOp()) {
1046 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init:
1047 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_init:
1048 llvm_unreachable("Already handled!");
1049
1050 // There is only one libcall for compare an exchange, because there is no
1051 // optimisation benefit possible from a libcall version of a weak compare
1052 // and exchange.
1053 // bool __atomic_compare_exchange(size_t size, void *mem, void *expected,
1054 // void *desired, int success, int failure)
1055 // bool __atomic_compare_exchange_N(T *mem, T *expected, T desired,
1056 // int success, int failure)
1057 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
1058 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
1059 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_weak:
1060 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_compare_exchange_strong:
1061 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange:
1062 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange_n:
1063 LibCallName = "__atomic_compare_exchange";
1064 RetTy = getContext().BoolTy;
1065 HaveRetTy = true;
1066 Args.add(
1067 RValue::get(CastToGenericAddrSpace(
1068 EmitCastToVoidPtr(Val1.getPointer()), E->getVal1()->getType())),
1069 getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1070 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val2.getPointer(),
1071 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1072 Args.add(RValue::get(Order), getContext().IntTy);
1073 Order = OrderFail;
1074 break;
1075 // void __atomic_exchange(size_t size, void *mem, void *val, void *return,
1076 // int order)
1077 // T __atomic_exchange_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1078 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_exchange:
1079 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_exchange:
1080 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange_n:
1081 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_exchange:
1082 LibCallName = "__atomic_exchange";
1083 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1084 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1085 break;
1086 // void __atomic_store(size_t size, void *mem, void *val, int order)
1087 // void __atomic_store_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1088 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store:
1089 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_store:
1090 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store:
1091 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_store_n:
1092 LibCallName = "__atomic_store";
1093 RetTy = getContext().VoidTy;
1094 HaveRetTy = true;
1095 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1096 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1097 break;
1098 // void __atomic_load(size_t size, void *mem, void *return, int order)
1099 // T __atomic_load_N(T *mem, int order)
1100 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load:
1101 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_load:
1102 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load:
1103 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_load_n:
1104 LibCallName = "__atomic_load";
1105 break;
1106 // T __atomic_add_fetch_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1107 // T __atomic_fetch_add_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1108 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_add_fetch:
1109 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Add;
1110 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1111 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_add:
1112 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_add:
1113 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_add:
1114 LibCallName = "__atomic_fetch_add";
1115 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1116 LoweredMemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1117 break;
1118 // T __atomic_and_fetch_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1119 // T __atomic_fetch_and_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1120 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_and_fetch:
1121 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::And;
1122 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1123 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_and:
1124 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_and:
1125 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_and:
1126 LibCallName = "__atomic_fetch_and";
1127 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1128 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1129 break;
1130 // T __atomic_or_fetch_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1131 // T __atomic_fetch_or_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1132 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_or_fetch:
1133 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Or;
1134 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1135 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_or:
1136 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_or:
1137 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_or:
1138 LibCallName = "__atomic_fetch_or";
1139 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1140 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1141 break;
1142 // T __atomic_sub_fetch_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1143 // T __atomic_fetch_sub_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1144 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_sub_fetch:
1145 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Sub;
1146 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1147 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_sub:
1148 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_sub:
1149 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_sub:
1150 LibCallName = "__atomic_fetch_sub";
1151 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1152 LoweredMemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1153 break;
1154 // T __atomic_xor_fetch_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1155 // T __atomic_fetch_xor_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1156 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_xor_fetch:
1157 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::Xor;
1158 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1159 case AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_fetch_xor:
1160 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_xor:
1161 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_xor:
1162 LibCallName = "__atomic_fetch_xor";
1163 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1164 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1165 break;
1166 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_min:
1167 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_min:
1168 LibCallName = E->getValueType()->isSignedIntegerType()
1169 ? "__atomic_fetch_min"
1170 : "__atomic_fetch_umin";
1171 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1172 LoweredMemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1173 break;
1174 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_max:
1175 case AtomicExpr::AO__opencl_atomic_fetch_max:
1176 LibCallName = E->getValueType()->isSignedIntegerType()
1177 ? "__atomic_fetch_max"
1178 : "__atomic_fetch_umax";
1179 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1180 LoweredMemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1181 break;
1182 // T __atomic_nand_fetch_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1183 // T __atomic_fetch_nand_N(T *mem, T val, int order)
1184 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch:
1185 PostOp = llvm::Instruction::And; // the NOT is special cased below
1186 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
1187 case AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_fetch_nand:
1188 LibCallName = "__atomic_fetch_nand";
1189 AddDirectArgument(*this, Args, UseOptimizedLibcall, Val1.getPointer(),
1190 MemTy, E->getExprLoc(), sizeChars);
1191 break;
1192 }
1193
1194 if (E->isOpenCL()) {
1195 LibCallName = std::string("__opencl") +
1196 StringRef(LibCallName).drop_front(1).str();
1197
1198 }
1199 // Optimized functions have the size in their name.
1200 // XXXAR: for capability libcalls we use _cap as the suffix
1201 if (UseOptimizedLibcall)
1202 LibCallName += IsCheriCap ? "_cap" : ("_" + llvm::utostr(Size));
1203 // By default, assume we return a value of the atomic type.
1204 if (!HaveRetTy) {
1205 if (UseOptimizedLibcall) {
1206 // Value is returned directly.
1207 // The function returns an appropriately sized integer type.
1208 RetTy = IsCheriCap
1209 ? getContext().UnsignedIntCapTy
1210 : getContext().getIntTypeForBitwidth(
1211 getContext().toBits(sizeChars), /*Signed=*/false);
1212 } else {
1213 // Value is returned through parameter before the order.
1214 RetTy = getContext().VoidTy;
1215 Args.add(RValue::get(EmitCastToVoidPtr(Dest.getPointer())),
1216 getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1217 }
1218 }
1219 // order is always the last parameter
1220 Args.add(RValue::get(Order),
1221 getContext().IntTy);
1222 if (E->isOpenCL())
1223 Args.add(RValue::get(Scope), getContext().IntTy);
1224
1225 // PostOp is only needed for the atomic_*_fetch operations, and
1226 // thus is only needed for and implemented in the
1227 // UseOptimizedLibcall codepath.
1228 assert(UseOptimizedLibcall || !PostOp);
1229
1230 RValue Res = emitAtomicLibcall(*this, LibCallName, RetTy, Args);
1231 // The value is returned directly from the libcall.
1232 if (E->isCmpXChg())
1233 return Res;
1234
1235 // The value is returned directly for optimized libcalls but the expr
1236 // provided an out-param.
1237 if (UseOptimizedLibcall && Res.getScalarVal()) {
1238 llvm::Value *ResVal = Res.getScalarVal();
1239 if (PostOp) {
1240 llvm::Value *LoadVal1 = Args[1].getRValue(*this).getScalarVal();
1241 ResVal = Builder.CreateBinOp(PostOp, ResVal, LoadVal1);
1242 }
1243 if (E->getOp() == AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_nand_fetch)
1244 ResVal = Builder.CreateNot(ResVal);
1245
1246 Builder.CreateStore(
1247 ResVal,
1248 Builder.CreateBitCast(Dest, ResVal->getType()->getPointerTo(
1249 CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS())));
1250 }
1251
1252 if (RValTy->isVoidType())
1253 return RValue::get(nullptr);
1254
1255 unsigned AS = Dest.getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
1256 return convertTempToRValue(
1257 Builder.CreateBitCast(Dest,
1258 ConvertTypeForMem(RValTy)->getPointerTo(AS)),
1259 RValTy, E->getExprLoc());
1260 }
1261
1262 if (isa<llvm::ConstantInt>(Order)) {
1263 auto ord = cast<llvm::ConstantInt>(Order)->getZExtValue();
1264 // We should not ever get to a case where the ordering isn't a valid C ABI
1265 // value, but it's hard to enforce that in general.
1266 if (llvm::isValidAtomicOrderingCABI(ord))
1267 switch ((llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI)ord) {
1268 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::relaxed:
1269 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1270 llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, Scope);
1271 break;
1272 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume:
1273 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire:
1274 if (IsStore)
1275 break; // Avoid crashing on code with undefined behavior
1276 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1277 llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire, Scope);
1278 break;
1279 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::release:
1280 if (IsLoad)
1281 break; // Avoid crashing on code with undefined behavior
1282 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1283 llvm::AtomicOrdering::Release, Scope);
1284 break;
1285 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel:
1286 if (IsLoad || IsStore)
1287 break; // Avoid crashing on code with undefined behavior
1288 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1289 llvm::AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease, Scope);
1290 break;
1291 case llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::seq_cst:
1292 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1293 llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent, Scope);
1294 break;
1295 }
1296 if (RValTy->isVoidType())
1297 return RValue::get(nullptr);
1298
1299 return convertTempToRValue(
1300 Builder.CreateBitCast(Dest, ConvertTypeForMem(RValTy)->getPointerTo(
1301 Dest.getAddressSpace())),
1302 RValTy, E->getExprLoc());
1303 }
1304
1305 // Long case, when Order isn't obviously constant.
1306
1307 // Create all the relevant BB's
1308 llvm::BasicBlock *MonotonicBB = nullptr, *AcquireBB = nullptr,
1309 *ReleaseBB = nullptr, *AcqRelBB = nullptr,
1310 *SeqCstBB = nullptr;
1311 MonotonicBB = createBasicBlock("monotonic", CurFn);
1312 if (!IsStore)
1313 AcquireBB = createBasicBlock("acquire", CurFn);
1314 if (!IsLoad)
1315 ReleaseBB = createBasicBlock("release", CurFn);
1316 if (!IsLoad && !IsStore)
1317 AcqRelBB = createBasicBlock("acqrel", CurFn);
1318 SeqCstBB = createBasicBlock("seqcst", CurFn);
1319 llvm::BasicBlock *ContBB = createBasicBlock("atomic.continue", CurFn);
1320
1321 // Create the switch for the split
1322 // MonotonicBB is arbitrarily chosen as the default case; in practice, this
1323 // doesn't matter unless someone is crazy enough to use something that
1324 // doesn't fold to a constant for the ordering.
1325 Order = Builder.CreateIntCast(Order, Builder.getInt32Ty(), false);
1326 llvm::SwitchInst *SI = Builder.CreateSwitch(Order, MonotonicBB);
1327
1328 // Emit all the different atomics
1329 Builder.SetInsertPoint(MonotonicBB);
1330 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1331 llvm::AtomicOrdering::Monotonic, Scope);
1332 Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
1333 if (!IsStore) {
1334 Builder.SetInsertPoint(AcquireBB);
1335 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1336 llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire, Scope);
1337 Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
1338 SI->addCase(Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::consume),
1339 AcquireBB);
1340 SI->addCase(Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acquire),
1341 AcquireBB);
1342 }
1343 if (!IsLoad) {
1344 Builder.SetInsertPoint(ReleaseBB);
1345 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1346 llvm::AtomicOrdering::Release, Scope);
1347 Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
1348 SI->addCase(Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::release),
1349 ReleaseBB);
1350 }
1351 if (!IsLoad && !IsStore) {
1352 Builder.SetInsertPoint(AcqRelBB);
1353 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1354 llvm::AtomicOrdering::AcquireRelease, Scope);
1355 Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
1356 SI->addCase(Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::acq_rel),
1357 AcqRelBB);
1358 }
1359 Builder.SetInsertPoint(SeqCstBB);
1360 EmitAtomicOp(*this, E, Dest, Ptr, Val1, Val2, IsWeak, OrderFail, Size,
1361 llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent, Scope);
1362 Builder.CreateBr(ContBB);
1363 SI->addCase(Builder.getInt32((int)llvm::AtomicOrderingCABI::seq_cst),
1364 SeqCstBB);
1365
1366 // Cleanup and return
1367 Builder.SetInsertPoint(ContBB);
1368 if (RValTy->isVoidType())
1369 return RValue::get(nullptr);
1370
1371 assert(Atomics.getValueSizeInBits() <= Atomics.getAtomicSizeInBits());
1372 return convertTempToRValue(
1373 Builder.CreateBitCast(Dest, ConvertTypeForMem(RValTy)->getPointerTo(
1374 Dest.getAddressSpace())),
1375 RValTy, E->getExprLoc());
1376}
1377
1378Address AtomicInfo::emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Address addr) const {
1379 Address Result = Address::invalid();
1380 unsigned addrspace;
1381 auto addrTy = cast<llvm::PointerType>(addr.getPointer()->getType());
1382 llvm::Type *ty;
1383 if (AtomicTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
1384 if (!UseLibcall) {
1385 // If we aren't using a libcall there is no need to cast to i8*
1386 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(addr, getAtomicPointer()->getType());
1387 // return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast();
1388 }
1389 // For libcalls we cast to an i8*
1390 // XXXAR: getDefaultAS and NOT getCheriCapabilityAS() since this should
1391 // also work in hybrid mode
1392 addrspace = CGF.CGM.getTargetCodeGenInfo().getDefaultAS();
1393 ty = CGF.Int8Ty;
1394 } else {
1395 ty = llvm::IntegerType::get(CGF.getLLVMContext(), AtomicSizeInBits);
1396 addrspace = addrTy->getAddressSpace();
1397 }
1398 Result = CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(addr, ty->getPointerTo(addrspace));
1399 return Result;
1400}
1401
1402Address AtomicInfo::convertToAtomicIntPointer(Address Addr) const {
1403 llvm::Type *Ty = Addr.getElementType();
1404 // correctly convert fetch_add, etc arguments:
1405 if (AtomicTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext()) && Ty->isIntegerTy()) {
1406 Addr = Address(CGF.setPointerAddress(
1407 llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(CGF.Int8CheriCapTy),
1408 CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr)), CGF.getContext().getTypeAlignInChars(AtomicTy));
1409 Ty = Addr.getPointer()->getType();
1410 }
1411 uint64_t SourceSizeInBits = CGF.CGM.getDataLayout().getTypeSizeInBits(Ty);
1412 if (SourceSizeInBits != AtomicSizeInBits) {
1413 Address Tmp = CreateTempAlloca();
1414 CGF.Builder.CreateMemCpy(Tmp, Addr,
1415 std::min(AtomicSizeInBits, SourceSizeInBits) / 8);
1416 Addr = Tmp;
1417 }
1418
1419 return emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Addr);
1420}
1421
1422RValue AtomicInfo::convertAtomicTempToRValue(Address addr,
1423 AggValueSlot resultSlot,
1424 SourceLocation loc,
1425 bool asValue) const {
1426 if (LVal.isSimple()) {
1427 if (EvaluationKind == TEK_Aggregate)
1428 return resultSlot.asRValue();
1429
1430 // Drill into the padding structure if we have one.
1431 if (hasPadding())
1432 addr = CGF.Builder.CreateStructGEP(addr, 0);
1433
1434 // Otherwise, just convert the temporary to an r-value using the
1435 // normal conversion routine.
1436 return CGF.convertTempToRValue(addr, getValueType(), loc);
1437 }
1438 if (!asValue)
1439 // Get RValue from temp memory as atomic for non-simple lvalues
1440 return RValue::get(CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(addr));
1441 if (LVal.isBitField())
1442 return CGF.EmitLoadOfBitfieldLValue(
1443 LValue::MakeBitfield(addr, LVal.getBitFieldInfo(), LVal.getType(),
1444 LVal.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo()), loc);
1445 if (LVal.isVectorElt())
1446 return CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(
1447 LValue::MakeVectorElt(addr, LVal.getVectorIdx(), LVal.getType(),
1448 LVal.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo()), loc);
1449 assert(LVal.isExtVectorElt());
1450 return CGF.EmitLoadOfExtVectorElementLValue(LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(
1451 addr, LVal.getExtVectorElts(), LVal.getType(),
1452 LVal.getBaseInfo(), TBAAAccessInfo()));
1453}
1454
1455RValue AtomicInfo::ConvertIntToValueOrAtomic(llvm::Value *IntVal,
1456 AggValueSlot ResultSlot,
1457 SourceLocation Loc,
1458 bool AsValue) const {
1459 if (AtomicTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
1460 auto *ValTy = AsValue ? CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ValueTy)
1461 : getAtomicAddress().getType()->getPointerElementType();
1462 assert(ValTy->isPointerTy());
1463 return RValue::get(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(IntVal, ValTy));
1464 }
1465
1466 // Try not to in some easy cases.
1467 assert(IntVal->getType()->isIntegerTy() && "Expected integer value");
1468 if (getEvaluationKind() == TEK_Scalar &&
1469 (((!LVal.isBitField() ||
1470 LVal.getBitFieldInfo().Size == ValueSizeInBits) &&
1471 !hasPadding()) ||
1472 !AsValue)) {
1473 auto *ValTy = AsValue
1474 ? CGF.ConvertTypeForMem(ValueTy)
1475 : getAtomicAddress().getType()->getPointerElementType();
1476 if (ValTy->isIntegerTy()) {
1477 assert(IntVal->getType() == ValTy && "Different integer types.");
1478 return RValue::get(CGF.EmitFromMemory(IntVal, ValueTy));
1479 } else if (ValTy->isPointerTy())
1480 return RValue::get(CGF.Builder.CreateIntToPtr(IntVal, ValTy));
1481 else if (llvm::CastInst::isBitCastable(IntVal->getType(), ValTy))
1482 return RValue::get(CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(IntVal, ValTy));
1483 }
1484
1485 // Create a temporary. This needs to be big enough to hold the
1486 // atomic integer.
1487 Address Temp = Address::invalid();
1488 bool TempIsVolatile = false;
1489 if (AsValue && getEvaluationKind() == TEK_Aggregate) {
1490 assert(!ResultSlot.isIgnored());
1491 Temp = ResultSlot.getAddress();
1492 TempIsVolatile = ResultSlot.isVolatile();
1493 } else {
1494 Temp = CreateTempAlloca();
1495 }
1496
1497 // Slam the integer into the temporary.
1498 Address CastTemp = emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Temp);
1499 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(IntVal, CastTemp)
1500 ->setVolatile(TempIsVolatile);
1501
1502 return convertAtomicTempToRValue(Temp, ResultSlot, Loc, AsValue);
1503}
1504
1505void AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicLoadLibcall(llvm::Value *AddForLoaded,
1506 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, bool) {
1507 // void __atomic_load(size_t size, void *mem, void *return, int order);
1508 CallArgList Args;
1509 Args.add(RValue::get(getAtomicSizeValue()), CGF.getContext().getSizeType());
1510 Args.add(RValue::get(CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(getAtomicPointer())),
1511 CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1512 Args.add(RValue::get(CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(AddForLoaded)),
1513 CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1514 Args.add(
1515 RValue::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntTy, (int)llvm::toCABI(AO))),
1516 CGF.getContext().IntTy);
1517 emitAtomicLibcall(CGF, "__atomic_load", CGF.getContext().VoidTy, Args);
1518}
1519
1520llvm::Value *AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicLoadOp(llvm::AtomicOrdering AO,
1521 bool IsVolatile) {
1522 // Okay, we're doing this natively.
1523 Address Addr = getAtomicAddressAsAtomicIntPointer();
1524 llvm::LoadInst *Load = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr, "atomic-load");
1525 Load->setAtomic(AO);
1526
1527 // Other decoration.
1528 if (IsVolatile)
1529 Load->setVolatile(true);
1530 CGF.CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(Load, LVal.getTBAAInfo());
1531 return Load;
1532}
1533
1534/// An LValue is a candidate for having its loads and stores be made atomic if
1535/// we are operating under /volatile:ms *and* the LValue itself is volatile and
1536/// performing such an operation can be performed without a libcall.
1537bool CodeGenFunction::LValueIsSuitableForInlineAtomic(LValue LV) {
1538 if (!CGM.getCodeGenOpts().MSVolatile) return false;
1539 AtomicInfo AI(*this, LV, AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load);
1540 bool IsVolatile = LV.isVolatile() || hasVolatileMember(LV.getType());
1541 // An atomic is inline if we don't need to use a libcall.
1542 bool AtomicIsInline = !AI.shouldUseLibcall();
1543 // MSVC doesn't seem to do this for types wider than a pointer.
1544 if (getContext().getTypeSize(LV.getType()) >
1545 getContext().getTypeSize(getContext().getIntPtrType()))
1546 return false;
1547 return IsVolatile && AtomicIsInline;
1548}
1549
1550RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicLoad(LValue LV, SourceLocation SL,
1551 AggValueSlot Slot) {
1552 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO;
1553 bool IsVolatile = LV.isVolatileQualified();
1554 if (LV.getType()->isAtomicType()) {
1555 AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
1556 } else {
1557 AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Acquire;
1558 IsVolatile = true;
1559 }
1560 return EmitAtomicLoad(LV, SL, AO, IsVolatile, Slot);
1561}
1562
1563RValue AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicLoad(AggValueSlot ResultSlot, SourceLocation Loc,
1564 bool AsValue, llvm::AtomicOrdering AO,
1565 bool IsVolatile) {
1566 // Check whether we should use a library call.
1567 if (shouldUseLibcall()) {
1568 Address TempAddr = Address::invalid();
1569 if (LVal.isSimple() && !ResultSlot.isIgnored()) {
1570 assert(getEvaluationKind() == TEK_Aggregate);
1571 TempAddr = ResultSlot.getAddress();
1572 } else
1573 TempAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1574
1575 EmitAtomicLoadLibcall(TempAddr.getPointer(), AO, IsVolatile);
1576
1577 // Okay, turn that back into the original value or whole atomic (for
1578 // non-simple lvalues) type.
1579 return convertAtomicTempToRValue(TempAddr, ResultSlot, Loc, AsValue);
1580 }
1581
1582 // Okay, we're doing this natively.
1583 auto *Load = EmitAtomicLoadOp(AO, IsVolatile);
1584
1585 // If we're ignoring an aggregate return, don't do anything.
1586 if (getEvaluationKind() == TEK_Aggregate && ResultSlot.isIgnored())
1587 return RValue::getAggregate(Address::invalid(), false);
1588
1589 // Okay, turn that back into the original value or atomic (for non-simple
1590 // lvalues) type.
1591 return ConvertIntToValueOrAtomic(Load, ResultSlot, Loc, AsValue);
1592}
1593
1594/// Emit a load from an l-value of atomic type. Note that the r-value
1595/// we produce is an r-value of the atomic *value* type.
1596RValue CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicLoad(LValue src, SourceLocation loc,
1597 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, bool IsVolatile,
1598 AggValueSlot resultSlot) {
1599 AtomicInfo Atomics(*this, src, AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_load);
1600 return Atomics.EmitAtomicLoad(resultSlot, loc, /*AsValue=*/true, AO,
1601 IsVolatile);
1602}
1603
1604/// Copy an r-value into memory as part of storing to an atomic type.
1605/// This needs to create a bit-pattern suitable for atomic operations.
1606void AtomicInfo::emitCopyIntoMemory(RValue rvalue) const {
1607 assert(LVal.isSimple());
1608 // If we have an r-value, the rvalue should be of the atomic type,
1609 // which means that the caller is responsible for having zeroed
1610 // any padding. Just do an aggregate copy of that type.
1611 if (rvalue.isAggregate()) {
1612 LValue Dest = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(getAtomicAddress(), getAtomicType());
1613 LValue Src = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(rvalue.getAggregateAddress(),
1614 getAtomicType());
1615 bool IsVolatile = rvalue.isVolatileQualified() ||
1616 LVal.isVolatileQualified();
1617 CGF.EmitAggregateCopy(Dest, Src, getAtomicType(),
1618 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap, IsVolatile);
1619 return;
1620 }
1621
1622 // Okay, otherwise we're copying stuff.
1623
1624 // Zero out the buffer if necessary.
1625 emitMemSetZeroIfNecessary();
1626
1627 // Drill past the padding if present.
1628 LValue TempLVal = projectValue();
1629
1630 // Okay, store the rvalue in.
1631 if (rvalue.isScalar()) {
1632 CGF.EmitStoreOfScalar(rvalue.getScalarVal(), TempLVal, /*init*/ true);
1633 } else {
1634 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(rvalue.getComplexVal(), TempLVal, /*init*/ true);
1635 }
1636}
1637
1638
1639/// Materialize an r-value into memory for the purposes of storing it
1640/// to an atomic type.
1641Address AtomicInfo::materializeRValue(RValue rvalue) const {
1642 // Aggregate r-values are already in memory, and EmitAtomicStore
1643 // requires them to be values of the atomic type.
1644 if (rvalue.isAggregate())
1645 return rvalue.getAggregateAddress();
1646
1647 // Otherwise, make a temporary and materialize into it.
1648 LValue TempLV = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(CreateTempAlloca(), getAtomicType());
1649 AtomicInfo Atomics(CGF, TempLV, AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store);
1650 Atomics.emitCopyIntoMemory(rvalue);
1651 return TempLV.getAddress();
1652}
1653
1654llvm::Value *AtomicInfo::convertRValueToInt(RValue RVal) const {
1655 // If we've got a scalar value of the right size, try to avoid going
1656 // through memory.
1657 if (RVal.isScalar() && (!hasPadding() || !LVal.isSimple())) {
1658 llvm::Value *Value = RVal.getScalarVal();
1659 if (isa<llvm::IntegerType>(Value->getType()))
1660 return CGF.EmitToMemory(Value, ValueTy);
1661 else {
1662 if (AtomicTy->isCHERICapabilityType(CGF.getContext())) {
1663 // Cast to the atomic ptr element type for CHERI capabilities
1664 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, LVal.getAddress().getElementType());
1665 }
1666 llvm::IntegerType *InputIntTy = llvm::IntegerType::get(
1667 CGF.getLLVMContext(),
1668 LVal.isSimple() ? getValueSizeInBits() : getAtomicSizeInBits());
1669 if (isa<llvm::PointerType>(Value->getType()))
1670 return CGF.Builder.CreatePtrToInt(Value, InputIntTy);
1671 else if (llvm::BitCastInst::isBitCastable(Value->getType(), InputIntTy))
1672 return CGF.Builder.CreateBitCast(Value, InputIntTy);
1673 }
1674 }
1675 // Otherwise, we need to go through memory.
1676 // Put the r-value in memory.
1677 Address Addr = materializeRValue(RVal);
1678
1679 // Cast the temporary to the atomic int type and pull a value out.
1680 Addr = emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(Addr);
1681 return CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(Addr);
1682}
1683
1684std::pair<llvm::Value *, llvm::Value *> AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicCompareExchangeOp(
1685 llvm::Value *ExpectedVal, llvm::Value *DesiredVal,
1686 llvm::AtomicOrdering Success, llvm::AtomicOrdering Failure, bool IsWeak) {
1687 // Do the atomic store.
1688 Address Addr = getAtomicAddressAsAtomicIntPointer();
1689 auto *Inst = CGF.Builder.CreateAtomicCmpXchg(Addr.getPointer(),
1690 ExpectedVal, DesiredVal,
1691 Success, Failure);
1692 // Other decoration.
1693 Inst->setVolatile(LVal.isVolatileQualified());
1694 Inst->setWeak(IsWeak);
1695
1696 // Okay, turn that back into the original value type.
1697 auto *PreviousVal = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractValue(Inst, /*Idxs=*/0);
1698 auto *SuccessFailureVal = CGF.Builder.CreateExtractValue(Inst, /*Idxs=*/1);
1699 return std::make_pair(PreviousVal, SuccessFailureVal);
1700}
1701
1702llvm::Value *
1703AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicCompareExchangeLibcall(llvm::Value *ExpectedAddr,
1704 llvm::Value *DesiredAddr,
1705 llvm::AtomicOrdering Success,
1706 llvm::AtomicOrdering Failure) {
1707 // bool __atomic_compare_exchange(size_t size, void *obj, void *expected,
1708 // void *desired, int success, int failure);
1709 CallArgList Args;
1710 Args.add(RValue::get(getAtomicSizeValue()), CGF.getContext().getSizeType());
1711 Args.add(RValue::get(CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(getAtomicPointer())),
1712 CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1713 Args.add(RValue::get(CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(ExpectedAddr)),
1714 CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1715 Args.add(RValue::get(CGF.EmitCastToVoidPtr(DesiredAddr)),
1716 CGF.getContext().VoidPtrTy);
1717 Args.add(RValue::get(
1718 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntTy, (int)llvm::toCABI(Success))),
1719 CGF.getContext().IntTy);
1720 Args.add(RValue::get(
1721 llvm::ConstantInt::get(CGF.IntTy, (int)llvm::toCABI(Failure))),
1722 CGF.getContext().IntTy);
1723 auto SuccessFailureRVal = emitAtomicLibcall(CGF, "__atomic_compare_exchange",
1724 CGF.getContext().BoolTy, Args);
1725
1726 return SuccessFailureRVal.getScalarVal();
1727}
1728
1729std::pair<RValue, llvm::Value *> AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
1730 RValue Expected, RValue Desired, llvm::AtomicOrdering Success,
1731 llvm::AtomicOrdering Failure, bool IsWeak) {
1732 if (isStrongerThan(Failure, Success))
1733 // Don't assert on undefined behavior "failure argument shall be no stronger
1734 // than the success argument".
1735 Failure = llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(Success);
1736
1737 // Check whether we should use a library call.
1738 if (shouldUseLibcall()) {
1739 // Produce a source address.
1740 Address ExpectedAddr = materializeRValue(Expected);
1741 Address DesiredAddr = materializeRValue(Desired);
1742 auto *Res = EmitAtomicCompareExchangeLibcall(ExpectedAddr.getPointer(),
1743 DesiredAddr.getPointer(),
1744 Success, Failure);
1745 return std::make_pair(
1746 convertAtomicTempToRValue(ExpectedAddr, AggValueSlot::ignored(),
1747 SourceLocation(), /*AsValue=*/false),
1748 Res);
1749 }
1750
1751 // If we've got a scalar value of the right size, try to avoid going
1752 // through memory.
1753 auto *ExpectedVal = convertRValueToInt(Expected);
1754 auto *DesiredVal = convertRValueToInt(Desired);
1755 auto Res = EmitAtomicCompareExchangeOp(ExpectedVal, DesiredVal, Success,
1756 Failure, IsWeak);
1757 return std::make_pair(
1758 ConvertIntToValueOrAtomic(Res.first, AggValueSlot::ignored(),
1759 SourceLocation(), /*AsValue=*/false),
1760 Res.second);
1761}

1763static void
1764EmitAtomicUpdateValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, AtomicInfo &Atomics, RValue OldRVal,
1765 const llvm::function_ref<RValue(RValue)> &UpdateOp,
1766 Address DesiredAddr) {
1767 RValue UpRVal;
1768 LValue AtomicLVal = Atomics.getAtomicLValue();
1769 LValue DesiredLVal;
1770 if (AtomicLVal.isSimple()) {
1771 UpRVal = OldRVal;
1772 DesiredLVal = CGF.MakeAddrLValue(DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getType());
1773 } else {
1774 // Build new lvalue for temp address.
1775 Address Ptr = Atomics.materializeRValue(OldRVal);
1776 LValue UpdateLVal;
1777 if (AtomicLVal.isBitField()) {
1778 UpdateLVal =
1779 LValue::MakeBitfield(Ptr, AtomicLVal.getBitFieldInfo(),
1780 AtomicLVal.getType(),
1781 AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(),
1782 AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1783 DesiredLVal =
1784 LValue::MakeBitfield(DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getBitFieldInfo(),
1785 AtomicLVal.getType(), AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(),
1786 AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1787 } else if (AtomicLVal.isVectorElt()) {
1788 UpdateLVal = LValue::MakeVectorElt(Ptr, AtomicLVal.getVectorIdx(),
1789 AtomicLVal.getType(),
1790 AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(),
1791 AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1792 DesiredLVal = LValue::MakeVectorElt(
1793 DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getVectorIdx(), AtomicLVal.getType(),
1794 AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(), AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1795 } else {
1796 assert(AtomicLVal.isExtVectorElt());
1797 UpdateLVal = LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(Ptr, AtomicLVal.getExtVectorElts(),
1798 AtomicLVal.getType(),
1799 AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(),
1800 AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1801 DesiredLVal = LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(
1802 DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getExtVectorElts(), AtomicLVal.getType(),
1803 AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(), AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1804 }
1805 UpRVal = CGF.EmitLoadOfLValue(UpdateLVal, SourceLocation());
1806 }
1807 // Store new value in the corresponding memory area.
1808 RValue NewRVal = UpdateOp(UpRVal);
1809 if (NewRVal.isScalar()) {
1810 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(NewRVal, DesiredLVal);
1811 } else {
1812 assert(NewRVal.isComplex());
1813 CGF.EmitStoreOfComplex(NewRVal.getComplexVal(), DesiredLVal,
1814 /*isInit=*/false);
1815 }
1816}
1817
1818void AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicUpdateLibcall(
1819 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, const llvm::function_ref<RValue(RValue)> &UpdateOp,
1820 bool IsVolatile) {
1821 auto Failure = llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(AO);
1822
1823 Address ExpectedAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1824
1825 EmitAtomicLoadLibcall(ExpectedAddr.getPointer(), AO, IsVolatile);
1826 auto *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont");
1827 auto *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_exit");
1828 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBB);
1829 Address DesiredAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1830 if ((LVal.isBitField() && BFI.Size != ValueSizeInBits) ||
1831 requiresMemSetZero(getAtomicAddress().getElementType())) {
1832 auto *OldVal = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(ExpectedAddr);
1833 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(OldVal, DesiredAddr);
1834 }
1835 auto OldRVal = convertAtomicTempToRValue(ExpectedAddr,
1836 AggValueSlot::ignored(),
1837 SourceLocation(), /*AsValue=*/false);
1838 EmitAtomicUpdateValue(CGF, *this, OldRVal, UpdateOp, DesiredAddr);
1839 auto *Res =
1840 EmitAtomicCompareExchangeLibcall(ExpectedAddr.getPointer(),
1841 DesiredAddr.getPointer(),
1842 AO, Failure);
1843 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Res, ExitBB, ContBB);
1844 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
1845}
1846
1847void AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicUpdateOp(
1848 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, const llvm::function_ref<RValue(RValue)> &UpdateOp,
1849 bool IsVolatile) {
1850 auto Failure = llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(AO);
1851
1852 // Do the atomic load.
1853 auto *OldVal = EmitAtomicLoadOp(AO, IsVolatile);
1854 // For non-simple lvalues perform compare-and-swap procedure.
1855 auto *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont");
1856 auto *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_exit");
1857 auto *CurBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
1858 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBB);
1859 llvm::PHINode *PHI = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(OldVal->getType(),
1860 /*NumReservedValues=*/2);
1861 PHI->addIncoming(OldVal, CurBB);
1862 Address NewAtomicAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1863 Address NewAtomicIntAddr = emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(NewAtomicAddr);
1864 if ((LVal.isBitField() && BFI.Size != ValueSizeInBits) ||
1865 requiresMemSetZero(getAtomicAddress().getElementType())) {
1866 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(PHI, NewAtomicIntAddr);
1867 }
1868 auto OldRVal = ConvertIntToValueOrAtomic(PHI, AggValueSlot::ignored(),
1869 SourceLocation(), /*AsValue=*/false);
1870 EmitAtomicUpdateValue(CGF, *this, OldRVal, UpdateOp, NewAtomicAddr);
1871 auto *DesiredVal = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(NewAtomicIntAddr);
1872 // Try to write new value using cmpxchg operation.
1873 auto Res = EmitAtomicCompareExchangeOp(PHI, DesiredVal, AO, Failure);
1874 PHI->addIncoming(Res.first, CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock());
1875 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Res.second, ExitBB, ContBB);
1876 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
1877}

1879static void EmitAtomicUpdateValue(CodeGenFunction &CGF, AtomicInfo &Atomics,
1880 RValue UpdateRVal, Address DesiredAddr) {
1881 LValue AtomicLVal = Atomics.getAtomicLValue();
1882 LValue DesiredLVal;
1883 // Build new lvalue for temp address.
1884 if (AtomicLVal.isBitField()) {
1885 DesiredLVal =
1886 LValue::MakeBitfield(DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getBitFieldInfo(),
1887 AtomicLVal.getType(), AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(),
1888 AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1889 } else if (AtomicLVal.isVectorElt()) {
1890 DesiredLVal =
1891 LValue::MakeVectorElt(DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getVectorIdx(),
1892 AtomicLVal.getType(), AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(),
1893 AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1894 } else {
1895 assert(AtomicLVal.isExtVectorElt());
1896 DesiredLVal = LValue::MakeExtVectorElt(
1897 DesiredAddr, AtomicLVal.getExtVectorElts(), AtomicLVal.getType(),
1898 AtomicLVal.getBaseInfo(), AtomicLVal.getTBAAInfo());
1899 }
1900 // Store new value in the corresponding memory area.
1901 assert(UpdateRVal.isScalar());
1902 CGF.EmitStoreThroughLValue(UpdateRVal, DesiredLVal);
1903}

1905void AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicUpdateLibcall(llvm::AtomicOrdering AO,
1906 RValue UpdateRVal, bool IsVolatile) {
1907 auto Failure = llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(AO);
1908
1909 Address ExpectedAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1910
1911 EmitAtomicLoadLibcall(ExpectedAddr.getPointer(), AO, IsVolatile);
1912 auto *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont");
1913 auto *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_exit");
1914 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBB);
1915 Address DesiredAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1916 if ((LVal.isBitField() && BFI.Size != ValueSizeInBits) ||
1917 requiresMemSetZero(getAtomicAddress().getElementType())) {
1918 auto *OldVal = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(ExpectedAddr);
1919 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(OldVal, DesiredAddr);
1920 }
1921 EmitAtomicUpdateValue(CGF, *this, UpdateRVal, DesiredAddr);
1922 auto *Res =
1923 EmitAtomicCompareExchangeLibcall(ExpectedAddr.getPointer(),
1924 DesiredAddr.getPointer(),
1925 AO, Failure);
1926 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Res, ExitBB, ContBB);
1927 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
1928}

1930void AtomicInfo::EmitAtomicUpdateOp(llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, RValue UpdateRVal,
1931 bool IsVolatile) {
1932 auto Failure = llvm::AtomicCmpXchgInst::getStrongestFailureOrdering(AO);
1933
1934 // Do the atomic load.
1935 auto *OldVal = EmitAtomicLoadOp(AO, IsVolatile);
1936 // For non-simple lvalues perform compare-and-swap procedure.
1937 auto *ContBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_cont");
1938 auto *ExitBB = CGF.createBasicBlock("atomic_exit");
1939 auto *CurBB = CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock();
1940 CGF.EmitBlock(ContBB);
1941 llvm::PHINode *PHI = CGF.Builder.CreatePHI(OldVal->getType(),
1942 /*NumReservedValues=*/2);
1943 PHI->addIncoming(OldVal, CurBB);
1944 Address NewAtomicAddr = CreateTempAlloca();
1945 Address NewAtomicIntAddr = emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(NewAtomicAddr);
1946 if ((LVal.isBitField() && BFI.Size != ValueSizeInBits) ||
1947 requiresMemSetZero(getAtomicAddress().getElementType())) {
1948 CGF.Builder.CreateStore(PHI, NewAtomicIntAddr);
1949 }
1950 EmitAtomicUpdateValue(CGF, *this, UpdateRVal, NewAtomicAddr);
1951 auto *DesiredVal = CGF.Builder.CreateLoad(NewAtomicIntAddr);
1952 // Try to write new value using cmpxchg operation.
1953 auto Res = EmitAtomicCompareExchangeOp(PHI, DesiredVal, AO, Failure);
1954 PHI->addIncoming(Res.first, CGF.Builder.GetInsertBlock());
1955 CGF.Builder.CreateCondBr(Res.second, ExitBB, ContBB);
1956 CGF.EmitBlock(ExitBB, /*IsFinished=*/true);
1957}

1978void CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicStore(RValue rvalue, LValue lvalue,
1979 bool isInit) {
1980 bool IsVolatile = lvalue.isVolatileQualified();
1981 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO;
1982 if (lvalue.getType()->isAtomicType()) {
1983 AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::SequentiallyConsistent;
1984 } else {
1985 AO = llvm::AtomicOrdering::Release;
1986 IsVolatile = true;
1987 }
1988 return EmitAtomicStore(rvalue, lvalue, AO, IsVolatile, isInit);
1989}
1990
1991/// Emit a store to an l-value of atomic type.
1992///
1993/// Note that the r-value is expected to be an r-value *of the atomic
1994/// type*; this means that for aggregate r-values, it should include
1995/// storage for any padding that was necessary.
1996void CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicStore(RValue rvalue, LValue dest,
1997 llvm::AtomicOrdering AO, bool IsVolatile,
1998 bool isInit) {
1999 // If this is an aggregate r-value, it should agree in type except
2000 // maybe for address-space qualification.
2001 assert(!rvalue.isAggregate() ||
2002 rvalue.getAggregateAddress().getElementType()
2003 == dest.getAddress().getElementType());
2004
2005 AtomicInfo atomics(*this, dest, AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_store);
2006 LValue LVal = atomics.getAtomicLValue();
2007
2008 // If this is an initialization, just put the value there normally.
2009 if (LVal.isSimple()) {
2010 if (isInit) {
2011 atomics.emitCopyIntoMemory(rvalue);
2012 return;
2013 }
2014
2015 // Check whether we should use a library call.
2016 if (atomics.shouldUseLibcall()) {
2017 // Produce a source address.
2018 Address srcAddr = atomics.materializeRValue(rvalue);
2019
2020 // void __atomic_store(size_t size, void *mem, void *val, int order)
2021 CallArgList args;
2022 args.add(RValue::get(atomics.getAtomicSizeValue()),
2023 getContext().getSizeType());
2024 args.add(RValue::get(EmitCastToVoidPtr(atomics.getAtomicPointer())),
2025 getContext().VoidPtrTy);
2026 args.add(RValue::get(EmitCastToVoidPtr(srcAddr.getPointer())),
2027 getContext().VoidPtrTy);
2028 args.add(
2029 RValue::get(llvm::ConstantInt::get(IntTy, (int)llvm::toCABI(AO))),
2030 getContext().IntTy);
2031 emitAtomicLibcall(*this, "__atomic_store", getContext().VoidTy, args);
2032 return;
2033 }
2034
2035 // Okay, we're doing this natively.
2036 llvm::Value *intValue = atomics.convertRValueToInt(rvalue);
2037
2038 // Do the atomic store.
2039 Address addr =
2040 atomics.emitCastToAtomicIntPointer(atomics.getAtomicAddress());
2041 intValue = Builder.CreateIntCast(
2042 intValue, addr.getElementType(), /*isSigned=*/false);
2043 llvm::StoreInst *store = Builder.CreateStore(intValue, addr);
2044
2045 // Initializations don't need to be atomic.
2046 if (!isInit)
2047 store->setAtomic(AO);
2048
2049 // Other decoration.
2050 if (IsVolatile)
2051 store->setVolatile(true);
2052 CGM.DecorateInstructionWithTBAA(store, dest.getTBAAInfo());
2053 return;
2054 }
2055
2056 // Emit simple atomic update operation.
2057 atomics.EmitAtomicUpdate(AO, rvalue, IsVolatile);
2058}

2060/// Emit a compare-and-exchange op for atomic type.
2061///
2062std::pair<RValue, llvm::Value *> CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicCompareExchange(
2063 LValue Obj, RValue Expected, RValue Desired, SourceLocation Loc,
2064 llvm::AtomicOrdering Success, llvm::AtomicOrdering Failure, bool IsWeak,
2065 AggValueSlot Slot) {
2066 // If this is an aggregate r-value, it should agree in type except
2067 // maybe for address-space qualification.
2068 assert(!Expected.isAggregate() ||
2069 Expected.getAggregateAddress().getElementType() ==
2070 Obj.getAddress().getElementType());
2071 assert(!Desired.isAggregate() ||
2072 Desired.getAggregateAddress().getElementType() ==
2073 Obj.getAddress().getElementType());
2074 AtomicInfo Atomics(*this, Obj, AtomicExpr::AO__atomic_compare_exchange);
2075
2076 return Atomics.EmitAtomicCompareExchange(Expected, Desired, Success, Failure,
2077 IsWeak);
2078}

2086
2087void CodeGenFunction::EmitAtomicInit(Expr *init, LValue dest) {
2088 AtomicInfo atomics(*this, dest, AtomicExpr::AO__c11_atomic_init);
2089
2090 switch (atomics.getEvaluationKind()) {
2091 case TEK_Scalar: {
2092 llvm::Value *value = EmitScalarExpr(init);
2093 atomics.emitCopyIntoMemory(RValue::get(value));
2094 return;
2095 }
2096
2097 case TEK_Complex: {
2098 ComplexPairTy value = EmitComplexExpr(init);
2099 atomics.emitCopyIntoMemory(RValue::getComplex(value));
2100 return;
2101 }
2102
2103 case TEK_Aggregate: {
2104 // Fix up the destination if the initializer isn't an expression
2105 // of atomic type.
2106 bool Zeroed = false;
2107 if (!init->getType()->isAtomicType()) {
2108 Zeroed = atomics.emitMemSetZeroIfNecessary();
2109 dest = atomics.projectValue();
2110 }
2111
2112 // Evaluate the expression directly into the destination.
2113 AggValueSlot slot = AggValueSlot::forLValue(dest,
2114 AggValueSlot::IsNotDestructed,
2115 AggValueSlot::DoesNotNeedGCBarriers,
2116 AggValueSlot::IsNotAliased,
2117 AggValueSlot::DoesNotOverlap,
2118 Zeroed ? AggValueSlot::IsZeroed :
2119 AggValueSlot::IsNotZeroed);
2120
2121 EmitAggExpr(init, slot);
2122 return;
2123 }
2124 }
2125 llvm_unreachable("bad evaluation kind");
2126}
